Definition: glyceride occurring naturally in animal and vegetable tissues
Example: it consists of three individual fatty acids bound together in a single large molecule; an important energy source forming much of the fat stored by the body
Synonyms: lipid, glyceride, fat, s, occurring, naturally, in, animal, and, vegetable, tissues, it, consists, of, three, individual, fatty, acids, bound, together, a, single, large, molecule, an, important, energy, source, forming, much, the, stored, by, body
Category: noun.substance
